President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring June 14, 2019, as Flag Day and the week starting June 9, 2019, as National Flag Week. The proclamation encourages all Americans to observe Flag Day and National Flag Week by displaying the American flag. It also urges citizens to honor America, celebrate its heritage, and publicly recite the Pledge of Allegiance during the period from Flag Day through Independence Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the American flag as a symbol of freedom, hope, and opportunity, and highlights the sacrifices made by men and women in uniform to defend it.